Liz Durrett (born 1978) is an American singer-songwriter born in Rome, Georgia and now based in Athens, Georgia.
She is currently signed to Athens-based Warm Records and has released three albums on the label.
Her first, Husk, was a collection of recordings from her teenage years recorded with Chesnutt between 1993 and 1996.
